  "text": "The arts and humanities were substantially under-represented within the core sustainability curricula, comprising only 6 % of the bachelor's and only 1 % of the master's required content (Fig. 3) , with only 22 % of master's and just over half (56 %) of bachelor's programs offering a core course in this category (Fig. 4) . [CITATION_1] also found few arts and humanities courses in sustainability programs, in particular noting that the few programs in her study that made explicit reference to sustainability lacked courses in philosophy.",
